<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <%- include('./partials/head.ejs') %>
     
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.6.0/css/all.min.css" integrity="sha512-Kc323vGBEqzTmouAECnVceyQqyqdsSiqLQISBL29aUW4U/M7pSPA/gEUZQqv1cwx4OnYxTxve5UMg5GT6L4JJg==" crossorigin="anonymous" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" />
    <style>       
    @import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:ital,wght@0,100;0,200;0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;0,800;0,900;1,100;1,200;1,300;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700;1,800;1,900&display=swap"); 
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            font-family: "Poppins", sans-serif;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* Main container */
        main {
            width: 90%;
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px 0;
        }

        /* Blog article styling */
        article {
            margin-top: 7rem;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        .share-section {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }

        .share-section p {
            font-size: 14px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .social-icons {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 15px;
        }

        .social-icons a {
            font-size: 24px;
            color: #007FB5;
        }

        /* Blog header */
        .blog-header h1 {
            margin-top: 1rem;
            font-size: 2rem;
            color: #333;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .blog-header p {
            margin-top: 25px;
            margin-left: 15px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            text-align: center;
            color: #666;
        }

        /* Blog image */
        .blog-image {
            width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
        }

        /* Blog content section */
        .blog-content {
            padding: 20px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .blog-content h2, .blog-content h3, .blog-content h4 {
            color: #007FB5;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        .blog-content h2 {
            font-size: 1.6rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .blog-content h3 {
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .blog-content h4 {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .blog-content p {
            margin: 15px 0;
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.8;
        }

        /* Lists inside the blog */
        .blog-content ul {
            margin: 15px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .blog-content ul li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            list-style-type: disc;
        }

        /* Responsive adjustments */
        @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
            main {
                width: 95%;
            }

            article {
                margin-top: 3rem;
            }

            .blog-header h1 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }

            .blog-content h2 {
                font-size: 1.4rem;
            }

            .blog-content h3 {
                font-size: 1.2rem;
            }

            .blog-content h4 {
                font-size: 1rem;
            }
        }

        @media screen and (max-width: 480px) {
            .blog-header h1 {
                font-size: 1.5rem;
            }

            .blog-content {
                padding: 10px;
            }

            .blog-content h2 {
                font-size: 1.3rem;
            }

            .blog-content h3 {
                font-size: 1.1rem;
            }

            .blog-content h4 {
                font-size: 1rem;
            }

            .blog-content p {
                font-size: 0.9rem;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Main Blog Content -->
    <%- include('./partials/nav.ejs') %>
    <main>
        <article>
            <!-- Blog Image -->
            <img src="images/blog/b1.png" alt="Educational Podcasts in 2024" class="blog-image">

            <!-- Blog Title and Meta Information -->
            <nav class="blog-header">
                <h1>The Rise of Educational Podcasts in 2024</h1>
                <p>By Grootz | October 2024</p>
            </nav>

            <!-- Blog Content -->
            <section class="blog-content">
                <h2>Introduction to Educational Podcasts</h2>
                <p>A podcast is a digital audio program that you can listen to on various devices, such as smartphones, tablets, or computers. Sometimes podcasts come in series, with episodes focusing on specific topics like news, storytelling, interviews, education, or entertainment. You can listen to podcasts anytime while doing some work, exercising, or relaxing.</p>
                
                <p>Educational podcasts are created to spread awareness, knowledge, or provide deep insights on different topics for addressing various interests and age groups. They cover many subjects, including science, history, personal development, technology, environment, and more. These podcasts often feature experts from different fields for interviews, discussions, lectures, or storytelling to enhance the listener's knowledge and understanding.</p>

                <h2>The Impact of Educational Podcasts in 2024</h2>
                <p>The impact of educational podcasts in 2024 is an ongoing trend in technology and educational fields. Here are some areas where educational podcasts have a notable impact:</p>

                <h3>1. Easy Accessibility</h3>
                <p>Educational podcasts continue to democratize access to information, allowing people from diverse backgrounds to learn at their own pace and on their schedules. This accessibility can help bridge educational gaps.</p>

                <h3>2. Global Availability</h3>
                <p>With the growth of the internet and mobile technology, educational podcasts can reach a global audience. This allows for the sharing of diverse perspectives and knowledge.</p>

                <h3>3. Variety</h3>
                <p>The variety of topics and formats available allows listeners to have learning experiences based on their interests and needs.</p>

                <h3>4. Building Community</h3>
                <p>Educational podcasts are a great way of creating communities with shared interests, which allow listeners to connect with like-minded individuals and engage in discussions beyond the podcast itself.</p>

                <h3>5. Self-Development</h3>
                <p>Podcasts are a great medium for continuous learning and skill development, making them an essential tool for staying updated in rapidly changing fields.</p>

                <h3>6. Mental Health and Well-Being</h3>
                <p>Some educational podcasts focus on personal development, mental health, and well-being, contributing to a holistic approach to education that considers emotional and psychological aspects.</p>

                <h2>Conclusion</h2>
                <p>Overall, educational podcasts in 2024 are likely to continue shaping how people learn, share knowledge, and engage with the world around them, making them an increasingly important tool in the landscape of education. Educational podcasts are a valuable resource for anyone looking to expand their knowledge or learn something new in an accessible format.</p>
            </section>
            <div class="share-section">
                <p>Share this Article</p>
                <div class="social-icons">
                    <a href="#" aria-label="Instagram">
                        <i class="fab fa-instagram"></i>
                    </a>
